{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1606293340,"nonce":"8ZFRHs4zRKGUH+cywMgREsHvDVY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3NTA2MTAxNDE=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3349","origin":"github"},"title":"SnpSift Filter needs option to specifiy --set dataset","message":"As reported in https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/how-to-restrict-vcf-variants-using-a-gene-list-with-the-set-function-in-snpsift, SnpSift Filter currently doesn't let you specify one or more datasets for the `--set` option of the command line tool.\n\nAs documented at https://pcingola.github.io/SnpEff/ss_filter/, sets are SnpSift's way to let a user specify a larger set of values to filter for in arbitrary filter expressions, like `\"( ID in SET[2] )\"`, which would retain variants with an ID matching any of the IDs listed in the second SET dataset.","files":null}]}